ng>David</strong> <strong>Zaslav</strong>. On Thursday, the company=E2=80=
=99s direct-to-consumer unit reported adjusted EBITDA of $677 million for 2=
024, up <em>exponentially</em> from $103 million the year before, plus stro=
ng performance from the Warners studio segment. Then, of course, there=E2=
=80=99s
the $19 billion that Zaz and C.F.O. <strong>Gunnar</strong> <strong>Wiedenf=
els</strong> have managed to shave off the company=E2=80=99s debt load in l=
ess than three years. Investor sentiment seems to be responding: In the pas=
t six months, the stock is up 51 percent, even though it=E2=80=99s still do=
wn 55 percent since the company was formed. So is the glass half empty or h=
