rcent since the company was formed nearly three years ago. Is the glass hal=
f empty or half full?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>That=E2=80=99s o=
ne of the most intriguing parlor games being played in Hollywood and on Wal=
l Street these days. Zaz, of course, remains supremely optimistic. =E2=80=
=9CWe really believe that the global players will be those that will really
prosper in the years ahead, and ultimately be the largest sustainable growt=
h media companies,=E2=80=9D he told Barclays analyst <strong>Kannan Venkate=
shwar </strong>on the earnings call. =E2=80=9CThere will probably be four, =
or five, or six, and our job every day is to fight to get a seat at that ta=
ble.=E2=80=9D The fourth quarter results, if they can be sustained, at leas=
t indicate that Zaz and WBD will likely be one of the =E2=80=9Cfour, five, =
or six.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
